															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/qntm" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(571081); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=571081&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227484" alt="qntm" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=571081)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/qntm" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(571081); return false;" >qntm</a></span> <span class="odate time_1554940161 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">10 Apr 2019 23:49</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4215330">
									

<p>Numerous thanks to editors Rimple, TheMightyMcB, HisShad0w and CryonicAutumn for reviewing various incarnations of this Tale and providing feedback.</p>
<p>Apologies for the long delay since the previous instalment, <a href="/immemorial">Immemorial</a>. This chapter was inordinately difficult to write because (as you might be able to tell) I know nothing whatever about touring as a professional concert violinist, and this chapter isn't really a complete story in itself, so I had a really annoying time trying to figure out a way to make it so that it wasn't just &quot;during a performance, SCP-3125 arrives, to be continued&quot;.</p>
<p>Towards the end of writing this I found I had too many different things I wanted to say and I had to cut a lot out for brevity, and I'm still not happy with how long the whole thing is. Notable omissions are: the Foundation's perspective on this incursion; interactions with the Ará Orún; the antagonist from <a href="/ojai">Ojai</a> doing evil things on international news and/or taunting Wheeler to his face about the fate of his wife; and, as devotees of my sandbox page will sadly recall, the &quot;burst flesh main&quot; scene.</p>
<p>As mentioned in the <a href="/antimemetics-division-timeline">Antimemetics Division Timeline</a>, and as alluded to towards the end of this chapter, this Tale takes place approximately one year after the events of <a href="/your-last-first-day">Your Last First Day</a>. We are finally out of flashback territory and proceeding with the story proper.</p>
<p>Some readers may recall my original pitch for Five Five Five Five Five: &quot;There's no Antimemetics Division. There's no Foundation. There's <em>nobody</em>.&quot;</p>

