    <div class="post-container" id="fpc-4216170">
                      
		<div class="post" id="post-4216170">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,4216170)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-4216170">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/qntm" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(571081); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=571081&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227484" alt="qntm" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=571081)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/qntm" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(571081); return false;" >qntm</a></span> <span class="odate time_1555014194 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">11 Apr 2019 20:23</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4216170">
									

<p>&quot;CASE HATE RED&quot; is a reference to a prior Antimemetics Division Tale, <em><a href="/case-colourless-green">CASE COLOURLESS GREEN</a></em>, which was a reference to both CASE NIGHTMARE GREEN (from the Stross books, yes, although I haven't read them) and to the famous grammatically correct but semantically meaningless sentence &quot;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Colorless_green_ideas_sleep_furiously">colourless green ideas sleep furiously</a>&quot;. Stross was referencing age-old military/political all-caps &quot;bad scenarios&quot; like BROKEN ARROW which are always nicely alarming in prose text.</p>
<p>SCP-3125, which is drawn in green pen in the chapter CASE COLOURLESS GREEN (and, in <em><a href="/ojai">Ojai</a></em>, apparently known by the codename &quot;Green&quot; by some in the Foundation), can be thought of as a &quot;sleeping idea&quot; due to its nature as a memeplex and its dormancy - but also &quot;colourless&quot;, since ideas don't really have colour, and &quot;furious&quot;, due to its hostility.</p>
<p>&quot;CASE HATE RED&quot; is obviously &quot;taking it to the next level&quot;. Here, we see that the shroud of secrecy has dropped and SCP-3125 is operating in the open. Also, in <em>Ojai</em>, we learned that &quot;Red&quot; is the codename not of the SCP-3125 cult but the man leading it. So there's some kind of connection there. Finally, &quot;HATE RED&quot; reads like &quot;HATRED&quot;, which is probably the closest single word we have in English for what SCP-3125 represents.</p>
<p>Most of my chapter titles do not have such an elaborate backstory!</p>

							</div>

								
