																		Hatred
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/lunardelta" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2898811); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2898811&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227484" alt="LunarDelta" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2898811)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/lunardelta" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2898811); return false;" >LunarDelta</a></span> <span class="odate time_1555145600 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">13 Apr 2019 08:53</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4217659">
									

<p>Fascinating! I have some questions though. Since the title for SCP-3125 is &quot;The Escapee&quot; I'm assuming it wasn't sent here on purpose, and that the hatred and violence it contains isn't necessarily directed at us per se, but rather is a natural part of whatever passes for culture or thought in its home dimension. I've always been curious about just where it came from. Do the people/creatures/entities there just go around constantly enraged and mutilating each other? Is their realm made of flesh and insects and cancer? Or are such perceptions nothing more than the feeble human brain trying to make sense of horrific higher-dimensional concepts?</p>
<p>Great chapter by the way. The nlth has finally hit the ftgn and you showed the horrific effects of that wonderfully.</p>

							</div>

								
